flow_state|05_Context|Flow State|Flow State describes the conditions under which attention becomes absorbed, effort feels steady, and progress starts to feel self-sustaining.|This domain looks at the conditions that make useful work easier to enter and easier to keep going across focus, ideas, movement, and conversation.|Read the ranked signals as likely flow conditions, not as a fixed identity. Lower-ranked signals are range to use deliberately, not weaknesses.|This is a ranked reading of the conditions most likely to help flow start, deepen, reset, and become useful.|active|flow_state::intro
06_Orientation
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|orientation_title|orientation_summary|score_shape_summary|rank_1_phrase|rank_2_phrase|rank_3_phrase|rank_4_phrase|status|lookup_key
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|balanced|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Deep focus first|Start by looking at Deep focus. Bring in ideas, expression, and new angles when the work needs more range.|Your scores are close together. Treat the ranking lightly and read this as a flexible flow profile.|Your main route is focused time with one demanding problem.|What adds energy: ideas, expression, and new angles.|What helps you reset: movement, pace, and a change of physical state.|What to use deliberately: conversation and feedback before the work becomes too private.|draft|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::balanced
07_Recognition
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|headline|recognition_statement|recognition_expansion|status|lookup_key
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|balanced|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Several ways into flow|You are likely to find flow through different conditions depending on the work in front of you.|Deep Focus appears first, but not by enough to make the result one-sided. You may use quiet concentration, fresh ideas, movement, or conversation at different points. The useful question is not which signal defines you. It is which condition the work needs now.|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::balanced
08_Signal_Roles
domain_key|signal_key|signal_label|rank_position|rank_role|title|description|productive_expression|risk_pattern|development_note|status|lookup_key
flow_state|deep_focus|Deep Focus|1|dominant|Deep Focus as a light starting point|Deep Focus is the first place to look, especially when the work needs attention, care, or enough time to settle. In this balanced result, it is a starting point rather than the whole route.|This can help you stay with the work long enough to see what matters.|The risk is treating focus as the answer when the task may need movement, a new angle, or another person.|Start with focus when the work needs depth, then check whether another condition would help it move.|active|flow_state::deep_focus::1
flow_state|creative_movement|Creative Movement|2|secondary|Creative Movement as a close option|Creative Movement is close enough to matter. It can help when the work needs ideas, alternatives, expression, or a different way through.|This can help you stop the work becoming too fixed, narrow, or over-controlled.|The risk is opening more possibilities when the work already needs a clearer choice.|Use ideas to widen the work when needed, then decide which angle is worth keeping.|active|flow_state::creative_movement::2
flow_state|physical_rhythm|Physical Rhythm|3|tertiary|Physical Rhythm as a useful change of state|Physical Rhythm gives this pattern a practical way to shift attention. Movement, pace, or a change of setting may help when sitting still is not helping.|This can help you reset energy, clear mental clutter, and return to the task with more steadiness.|The risk is missing the point where a physical reset would help, or staying active when the work now needs focus.|Bring in movement when the work feels stuck, heavy, or too mental.|active|flow_state::physical_rhythm::3
flow_state|social_exchange|Social Exchange|4|least_expressed|Social Exchange as deliberate range|Social Exchange sits fourth, but it is still meaningful in a balanced profile. Conversation, feedback, or shared thinking can help when the work needs testing outside your own view.|This can help you check whether the work makes sense to someone else.|The risk is using conversation too late, after you have already spent energy trying to solve everything alone.|Bring in one useful person when the work needs clarity, response, or a reality check.|active|flow_state::social_exchange::4
09_Pattern_Mechanics
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|mechanics_title|core_mechanism|why_it_shows_up|what_it_protects|status|lookup_key
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|balanced|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Why the route changes|This pattern works by giving the person several usable entry points into flow, rather than one fixed route.|It may show up because different kinds of work ask for different conditions. A demanding problem may need quiet focus. A blank page may need ideas. A heavy day may need movement. A decision may need conversation.|It protects adaptability. The trade-off is that the person may switch conditions too quickly instead of choosing the one that best fits the task.|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::balanced
10_Pattern_Synthesis
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|synthesis_title|gift|trap|takeaway|synthesis_text|status|lookup_key
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|balanced|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Flexible flow with a light first route|You can adapt how you enter flow depending on the work, the setting, and your energy.|You may keep changing conditions instead of giving one route enough time to work.|Choose the condition before you begin, then give it a fair chance.|This pattern is strongest when flexibility becomes deliberate. Deep Focus can help you settle into the work. Creative Movement can open a better angle. Physical Rhythm can change your state. Social Exchange can test the result with another person. The skill is choosing the right condition for the moment, not trying to use every route at once.|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::balanced
